{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Allows to select the balance between result accuracy (precision) and missed barcodes (recall) for linear barcodes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall."}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode"},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Enumeration-Cases","title":"Enumeration Cases","identifiers":["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode\/minimal","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode\/moderate","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode\/none","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode\/thorough"]},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode\/init(rawValue:)"]},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode\/Equatable-Implementations","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConf